mas but fell 0.2% in the final three months of the year. Food sales rose throughout but sales of clothing and other general goods fell 2.1% in the final quarter, though they rose slightly in the run-up to Christmas.</p><p>Bolland blamed an unusually warm October, which put people off buying winter clothes, for the fall in sales. However, retail analyst Nick Bubb said M&amp;S did not point this out at its half-year results in November.</p><p>M&amp;S said discounting had reduced its margins in general merchandise but that all its other  market guidance remained intact. Finance director Alan Stewart declined to give a figure for full-year profit expectations but Bubb said analysts' forecasts would be \"edging down\" after the trading update.</p><p>M&amp;S shares fell immediately after the company released its statement but the shares revived, rising just over 2% to 455p.</p><p></p><p>Bolland said sales in the all-important general merchandise business were going in the right direction. M&amp;S was one of a trio of large retailers to report worse than expected Christmas trading, as Tesco and Morrisons also fell short of forecasts.</p>","headline":"M&amp;S boss defends deep pre-Christmas discounts as sales fall short","trailText":"Marc Bolland says Marks &amp; Spencer was forced to react when competitors launched aggressive promotions to lure shoppers","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3yyh9","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Business/Pix/pictures/2014/1/9/1389263574500/Marks--Spencer-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Business/Pix/pictures/2014/1/9/1389263574500/Marks--Spencer-006.jpg","wordcount":"371","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"426651452","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8533919","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Sean Farrell","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-01-10T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2023443","produc